article.headline: Arizona State 65, Temple 62
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- There was a Kruger on the court, but it was Ike Diogu who made things a nightmare on Broad Street for the Temple Owls. Diogu scored 15 points and grabbed 16 rebounds, and Serge Angounou had 13 points and a career-high 14 rebounds to lead Arizona State to a 65-62 win over Temple on Tuesday night. Steve Moore added 13 points and Kevin Kruger had 12 for Arizona State. Temple (1-3) had its chances late in the game, but, much like what happened in its season-opening loss against Auburn, blew it with late mistakes and missed shots. The Owls had a chance to take the lead with 35 seconds left, but Dustin Salisbery turned the ball over. Arizona State (4-1) then sank a couple of free throws to go up three. After the two teams traded free throws to put Arizona State up 65-62, Salisbery shot a 3-pointer wide at the buzzer, allowing the Sun Devils to escape with the victory. The Sun Devils had a 53-38 rebounding advantage for the game against Temple's matchup zone defense. Leading the charge was Diogu, who had 13 of his rebounds in the first half. "One thing the zone can't stop you doing is going to the boards," Diogu said after the game. Temple coach John Chaney also agreed that the Sun Devils' work on the boards was the difference in the contest. "Not rebounding hurt us. They had 13 offensive rebounds in the first half. We've got to change that. Hopefully we'll grow by January, but we might have a lot of bruises by then," Chaney said. Mark Tyndale and Salisbery each scored 15 points for Temple. Antwayne Robinson had 11 points and Mardy Collins added 10 for the Owls.
